accessibility.note: The Accessibility module was never stable in Drupal 7, and has been unsupported for a long time. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

accessible_content.note: The Accessible Content module was never stable in Drupal 7, and has been unsupported for a long time. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

actions_permissions.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated.

adminrole.note: This module is a little helper to maintain an administrator role which has all available permissions for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

advanced_link.note: This module is obsolete in Drupal 9. No known equivalent module exists; please help porting this module if it's critical for your site

auto_height.note: This module needs an asset library that must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/auto_height.

bat_api.note: This module must be installed manually as it has library requirement conflict with drupal/date_recur module.

batch_jobs.note: This module is currently unmaintained. Use at your own risk. It's also seeking new maintainers.

better_exposed_filters.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

better_formats.note: The Better Formats module was never stable in Drupal 7. Most of its functionality is obsolete in Drupal 9.

blockcache_alter.note: This module has no use in Drupal 9: every block already has optimal caching built in.

bookkeeping.note: This module must be installed manually due to its dependency on drupal/dynamic_entity_reference development version.

bootstrap_modal_forms.note: The Bootstrap Modal Forms module was never stable in Drupal 7, and has been unsupported for a long time. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

browser_refresh.note: This module is not composer installable — see https://www.drupal.org/project/browser_refresh/issues/3241233.

bulk_export.note: The Bulk Export submodule of the CTools module is obsolete, because Drupal core now has a Configuration System built in.

bundle_copy.note: This module provides content type copying for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

cacheexclude.note: The list of paths for cache exclude needs manual re-evaluation to make sure that only the necessary paths are excluded.

calendar.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

chain_menu_access.note: Chain Menu Access API allows your module to chain its own menu access callback functions into other module's menu router entries. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

civicrm_entity.note: This module must be installed manually as it has requirement conflict with other modules.

ckeditor.note: This module provides WYSIWYG editing for rich text fields using CKEditor for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality, in the CKEditor module.

ckeditor_image2.note: This module provides the Enhanced Image plugin for CKEditor. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality, in the CKEditor module.

ckeditor_link_file.note: The actual migration is provided by the media_migration module.

clone.note: The Drupal 8 and above successors of this Drupal 7 module has very different settings. It now supports all entity types, not just nodes. You need to manually reconfigure the settings, the differences make an automated migration impossible. One often used capability in Drupal 7 is to automatically unpublish clones — this does not yet exist in Drupal 8 and above. If you want that, help out at https://www.drupal.org/project/entity_clone/issues/3036068.

colorbox_node.note: This module is obsolete in Drupal 9. Check if https://www.drupal.org/project/colorbox_simple_load or https://www.drupal.org/project/colorbox_load address your needs.

commerce_ccavenue.note: The Commerce CCAvenue Payment Gateway module has a stable Drupal 9 release but does not seem trustworthy. It claims to require the 'mcrypt' PHP extension. But that was dropped from PHP many years ago. Since https://www.drupal.org/project/commerce_ccavenue/issues/2998729 it no longer needs it, but it still claims it does. Install at your own risk. Please consider switching to an alternative module.

commerce_maxipago.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/commerce_maxipago for instructions.

commerce_payfort.note: This module claims to be Drupal 9-compatible but it is not - see https://www.drupal.org/project/commerce_payfort/issues/3229354.

commerce_realex.note: This module must be installed manually — see README.md for installation instructions.

commerce_vipps.note: This module must be installed manually as it has requirement conflict with drupal/acquia_search_solr's php-http/guzzle6-adapter library.

composer_manager.note: The Composer Manager module is obsolete in Drupal 9, it was only necessary in Drupal 7.

context.note: Most of the functionality in the Context for Drupal 7 module has been merged into Drupal core. If you want the remaining functionality, you could install it.

context_ui.note: Most of the functionality in the Context for Drupal 7 module has been merged into Drupal core. If you want the remaining functionality, you could install it.

contextly.note: This module claims to be Drupal 9-compatible but it is not composer-installable — see https://www.drupal.org/project/contextly/issues/3240244.

d8cache.note: The Drupal 8 Cache Backport module is obsolete in Drupal 9, it was only necessary in Drupal 7.

dashboard.note: The Dashboard module was marked obsolete by its maintainers.

dashboard_connector.note: The Dashboard Connector module was marked as obsolete by its maintainers. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

datatables.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you. We've preinstalled it for you though, so just go to /admin/config/system/encryption/profiles and configure it as needed.

metatags_quick.note: The Meta tags quick module was merged into the Metatag module. You can help finish the migration path at https://www.drupal.org/project/metatag/issues/2618898, https://www.drupal.org/project/metatag/issues/3082398 and https://www.drupal.org/project/metatag/issues/3082401.

migrate.note: The Drupal 7 migrate module should probably not have been installed on your production Drupal 7 site, unless you were using it to constantly migrate data from external data sources. You will need to port your custom code.

migrate_d2d.note: This module is only for migrating data from Drupal 5 or 6 into Drupal 7. It should never have been enabled on any Drupal 7 production site.

migrate_extras.note: This module is only for migrating data from Drupal 5 or 6 into Drupal 7. It should never have been enabled on any Drupal 7 production site.

migrate_ui.note: The Drupal 7 migrate module should probably not have been installed on your production Drupal 7 site, unless you were using it to constantly migrate data from external data sources. You will need to port your custom code.

mimemail_action.note: This module's functionality is built into Drupal 9 core: use the e-mail action.

missing_module.note: The Missing Module module for Drupal 7 is irrelevant in Drupal 9.

mnc.note: This module is not composer installable — see https://www.drupal.org/project/mnc/issues/3256094.

modal_forms.note: The Modal forms (with ctools) module's functionality is built into Drupal core - see https://www.drupal.org/docs/drupal-apis/ajax-api/ajax-dialog-boxes.

module_filter.note: Most of the functionality in the Module Filter for Drupal 7 module has been merged into Drupal core. If you want the remaining functionality, you could install it.

mongodb.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/mongodb.

multiblock.note: This module's functionality is built into Drupal 9 core.

multiform.note: This is an API module which lets you put several forms into one <form>. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality. See https://www.drupal.org/node/2774077.

multiupload_filefield_widget.note: This module's functionality is built into Drupal 9 core.

multiupload_imagefield_widget.note: This module's functionality is built into Drupal 9 core.

neo4j.note: The neo4j module is not composer installable. Help out at https://www.drupal.org/project/neo4j/issues/3229364.

node_clone.note: The Drupal 8 and above successors of this Drupal 7 module has very different settings. It now supports all entity types, not just nodes. You need to manually reconfigure the settings, the differences make an automated migration impossible. One often used capability in Drupal 7 is to automatically unpublish clones — this does not yet exist in Drupal 8 and above. If you want that, help out at https://www.drupal.org/project/entity_clone/issues/3036068.

node_clone_tab.note: The Drupal 8 and above successors of this Drupal 7 module has very different settings. It now supports all entity types, not just nodes. You need to manually reconfigure the settings, the differences make an automated migration impossible. One often used capability in Drupal 7 is to automatically unpublish clones — this does not yet exist in Drupal 8 and above. If you want that, help out at https://www.drupal.org/project/entity_clone/issues/3036068.

node_expire.note: This module is marked obsolete by its maintainers.

node_page_disable.note: The page /node is a Views view on Drupal 8 and above, so this can now be achieved by disabling the "Page" display of the "Frontpage" view at /admin/structure/views/view/frontpage/edit/page_1.

node_reference.note: This module provides a field type for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

notify_log.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/notify_log/issues/3242228

number.note: This module no longer exists because its field types have been merged into Drupal core's Field module.

openlayers.note: Module is not ready for use — see https://www.drupal.org/project/openlayers.

options_element.note: This module is obsolete in Drupal 8 and above. No known equivalent module exists; please help porting this module if it's critical for your site. See https://www.drupal.org/project/options_element/issues/2223583.

overlay.note: The new Drupal 8 and above toolbar now includes a contextually aware "back to site" button that serves the same use-case as overlay by allowing site users to return from the admin context to the page that they were on.

page_title.note: The Page Title module was merged into the Metatag module. You can help finish the migration path at https://www.drupal.org/project/metatag/issues/3077729 and https://www.drupal.org/project/metatag/issues/3077730.

panels.note: This migration is not yet automated, feel free to help in https://www.drupal.org/project/panels/issues/2296443.

panels_ipe.note: This migration is not yet automated, feel free to help in https://www.drupal.org/project/panels/issues/2296443.

panels_mini.note: The Mini panels submodule of the Panels module is obsolete, because Drupal core now has a rich block system, which combined with the Drupal 9 Layout Builder can do much more.

panels_node.note: The Panel nodes submodule of the Panels module is obsolete, because Drupal core now has a rich block system, which combined with the Drupal 9 Layout Builder can do much more.

panopoly_core.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly/issues/3249100.

panopoly_demo.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly/issues/3249100.

panopoly_images.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly/issues/3249100.

panopoly_pages.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly/issues/3249100.

panopoly_test.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly/issues/3249100.

panopoly_users.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly/issues/3249100.

panopoly_widgets.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly/issues/3249100.

panopoly_wysiwyg.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/panopoly_wysiwyg for instructions.

parallax_bg.note: This module needs an asset library that must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/parallax_bg.

paranoia.note: Drupal 7's PHP module is not recommended because it poses a severe security risk without very careful configuration and trusted users. Therefore you should not need the Paranoia module either.

pdf_html.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/pdf_html/issues/3240772

pdf_using_mpdf.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/pdf_using_mpdf/issues/3205270

php.note: Drupal 7's PHP module is not recommended because it poses a severe security risk without very careful configuration and trusted users.

phpword.note: This module must be installed manually as it has requirement conflict with other modules.

poll.note: The poll module is no longer part of Drupal core.

printfriendly.note: The PrintFriendly & PDF module was marked as obsolete by its maintainers. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

private_taxonomy.note: This module is currently unmaintained. Use at your own risk. It's also seeking new maintainers, see https://www.drupal.org/project/private_taxonomy/issues/3244798.

probo.note: Development of this project is moved to github. For more information see - https://www.drupal.org/project/probo.

profile.note: The profile module is no longer part of Drupal core. Before installing this module, you may wish to consider if you can use core modules to achieve the same functionality.

publishcontent.note: This module provides per-content type publishing permission for a Drupal 7 site. While this module does have a Drupal 9 compatible release, Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality since Drupal 9 is distributed with the Workflows and Content Moderation modules. These modules afford the ability to create per-content type workflows which contain "transitions" (e.g. from "draft" to "published") and permissions can be granted (or withheld) for those transitions.

quick_cache_cleaner.note: This module provides support for manually flushing caches. In Drupal 7 this was frequently necessary. But this is unnecessary in Drupal 9 thanks to cache tags: they ensure all pages are always up-to-date.

references.note: This module provides field types for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

rest_server.note: Drupal core is now shipped with the JSON:API and REST modules. In most cases, these completely replace the functionality of the REST Server module.

revisioning.note: This module provides an API for handling drafts of revisions in Drupal 7. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

rules.note: The Rules module's port to Drupal 8 and above is still in progress. An unstable pre-release version is available though.

rules_admin.note: The Rules module's port to Drupal 8 and above is still in progress. An unstable pre-release version is available though.

rules_i18n.note: The Rules module's port to Drupal 8 and above is still in progress. An unstable pre-release version is available though.

rules_scheduler.note: The Rules module's port to Drupal 8 and above is still in progress. An unstable pre-release version is available though.

safe_cache_form_clear.note: The Safe cache_form Clear module ships with Drupal 7.61 and with Drupal 8 & 9. It is obsolete on all versions of Drupal.

save_draft.note: Save Draft adds a 'Save as Draft' Button to the node_form for content types, allowing the user to click the 'Save as Draft' button to save the node as a draft. Drupal 8 and above has this UX feature in the core.

schemaorg.note: This module enables the collections of schemas available at schema.org in Drupal 7. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality. Note that you will need to manually configure the RDF mappings. You could do this once and export the configuration to avoid having to do this multiple times.

search_api.note: An automatic migration of settings does not make sense for this module. Migrating it as-is could also affect the (production) Drupal 7 site. Furthermore, the new search indexes likely need to be different. See https://www.drupal.org/docs/contributed-modules/search-api.

search_api_federated_solr.note: This module needs to be installed manually due to its version conflicts with https://www.drupal.org/project/search_api_solr

search_api_spellcheck.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

search_api_views.note: This module is part of the base Search API module since https://www.drupal.org/project/search_api/issues/2044411.

seckit.note: The security policies for a site depend on its front end and infrastructure. Also, Drupal 7 typically requires a relatively lax CSP policy because of inline scripts. Therefore migrating the configuration from Drupal 7 does not make sense. In most cases, you should be able to configure seckit to be more strict in Drupal 9 than in Drupal 7.

semanticviews.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

services.note: Drupal core is now shipped with the JSON:API and REST modules. In most cases, these completely replace the functionality of the services module.

services_documentation.note: Drupal core is now shipped with the JSON:API and REST modules. In most cases, these completely replace the functionality of the services module. To add documentation, install the https://www.drupal.org/project/openapi module.

services_views.note: Drupal core is now shipped with the REST module, with which 'REST Export displays' can be created. In most cases, these completely replace the functionality of the Services Views module.

session_api.note: This module provides set of functions that extend the core sessions workings, allowing data to be stored and associated with a user's session. Developers porting their modules using Session API to Drupal 8 and above are encouraged to switch to Symfony's Session Management. See https://symfony.com/doc/current/components/http_foundation/sessions.html.

shield.note: The list of paths for shield module needs manual re-evaluation to make sure that only the necessary paths are shielded.

signaturefield.note: This module must be installed manually — see README.md for installation instructions.

simplehtmldom.note: This module is abandoned and obsolete; use PHP's built-in https://www.php.net/manual/en/class.domdocument.php now!

simplemde.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/simplemde for instructions.

simplenews_scheduler.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/simplenews_scheduler/issues/3230858.

simpletest.note: SimpleTest has been deprecated and removed from Drupal core. PHPUnit is the officially supported testing library in Drupal 9.

simplified_menu_admin.note: This module simplifies the core Menu and Shortcut modules by merging the "List links" and "Edit menu" operations into a single administration page. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

site_verify.note: The Site Verify module never got any release for Drupal 8 and above. Per https://www.drupal.org/project/site_verify/issues/2194861#comment-11511471, it is recommended to install the Metatag Verification submodule of the Metatag module. Unfortunately, no migration path for this exists yet. Help at https://www.drupal.org/project/metatag/issues/3251874.

slick_views.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

sms_twilio.note: This module must be installed manually as it has requirement conflict with other modules.

social_wall.note: It is recommended to start from scratch, both for configuring this module and even whether to use this module. Consider using https://www.drupal.org/project/socialfeed instead, which has wider adoption.

sparkpost.note: This module must be installed manually as it has requirement conflict with drupal/acquia_search_solr module.

special_menu_items.note: The Special menu items module is obsolete because non-link menu items can now be specified using `route:<nolink>`.

statistics_counter.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

strongarm.note: The Strongarm module is obsolete, because Drupal core now has a Configuration System built in.

superfish.note: This module needs an asset library that must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/superfish. Also, the placed Drupal 7 Superfish blocks are not migrated to Drupal 9, because the Drupal 9 port of this module provides one block per menu that is ready for you to be placed. Migrating the detailed settings of the Drupal 7 block is pointless, because those depend on the theme, which you will have to port manually. In other words: all functionality is available to you, but a complete migration makes no sense.

swagger_ui_formatter.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/swagger_ui_formatter for instructions.

swiftmailer.note: Swiftmailer library will stop being maintained at the end of November 2021 - see https://www.drupal.org/project/swiftmailer/issues/3232819 and https://symfony.com/blog/the-end-of-swiftmailer.

system.note: This module is required for all Drupal sites.

taxonomy_title.note: The Taxonomy Title module is obsolete, because the Taxonomy term page is a view in Drupal core now, whose title can easily be modified.

teamleader.note: This module must be installed manually as it has requirement conflict with drupal/acquia_search_solr module.

title.note: The Title module is largely obsolete, because entity titles are translatable out of the box in Drupal 9. Only the ability to control the rendering of the title like any other field is not in Drupal core. See https://www.drupal.org/project/contrib_tracker/issues/2607758 for details.

tmgmt_morningside.note: This module is not composer installable - see https://www.drupal.org/project/tmgmt_morningside/issues/3240770

tracker.note: The Tracker migration is unfortunately not yet working correctly. Help out at https://www.drupal.org/project/drupal/issues/3204511.

transliteration.note: This module provides transliteration for machine names and file names for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a some of its functionality, but not file name transliteration. For that, an additional module must be installed: https://www.drupal.org/project/transliterate_filenames. Transliteration of filenames used to be necessary for compatibility, but nowadays all browsers and operating systems support unicode filenames. So it is most likely unnecessary.

trigger.note: The trigger module was removed from Drupal core and does not have a recommended replacement at this time.

tweet_feed.note: This module must be installed manually as it has requirement conflict with drupal/socialfeed module.

uc_pdf_invoice_mail.note: This module is not composer installable — see https://www.drupal.org/project/uc_pdf_invoice_mail/issues/3241226 for instructions.

url.note: Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

user_picture_field.note: This module allow you add an image field to user, and show it on user register form, after user register an account. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

user_reference.note: This module provides a field type for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

uuid.note: Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

uuid_path.note: Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

uuid_services.note: Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality.

varbase_editor.note: This module is not composer installable — see https://www.drupal.org/project/varbase_editor/issues/3186421 for instructions.

variable_realm.note: The Variable realm submodule of the Variable module is obsolete, because Drupal core now has a Configuration System built in.

variable_store.note: The Variable store submodule of the Variable module is obsolete, because Drupal core now has a Configuration System built in.

variable_views.note: The Variable views submodule of the Variable module is obsolete, because Drupal core now has a Configuration System built in.

vegas.note: This module needs an asset library that must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/vegas.

views_content_cache.note: Views in Drupal 9 are efficiently cached and guarantee instantaneous updates, out of the box, no extra modules needed.

views_json.note: The Views JSON module is obsolete, because Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality in its REST and JSON:API modules. When installing the REST module along with Views in Drupal 9, you can create 'REST Export' displays that output not HTML but JSON. An even better choice is to not use JSON-generating views (because there are significant limitations), but instead install the built-in JSON:API module. Install the JSON:API module in case you want to access entity data directly, install the REST module in case you want to apply various transformations from within Views first. See https://www.drupal.org/docs/core-modules-and-themes/core-modules/jsonapi-module/jsonapi-vs-cores-rest-module.

views_litepager.note: Drupal core includes this optimized pager implementation as the 'mini pager' since https://www.drupal.org/project/drupal/issues/1901290.

views_load_more.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

views_megarow.note: This module is obsolete in Drupal 8 and above - see https://www.drupal.org/project/views_megarow/issues/2492003.

views_queue.note: The Views Queue module was never stable in Drupal 7, and has been unsupported for a long time. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

views_responsive_grid.note: This module is obsolete in Drupal 8 and above - see https://www.drupal.org/project/views/issues/1903746.

views_slideshow_jcarousel.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/views_slideshow_jcarousel for instructions.

views_tree.note: This migration is not yet automated, because the migration of views is not yet automated. But the functionality is available, so we preinstalled it for you.

vimeo_link_formatter.note: No port is available, help in https://www.drupal.org/project/vimeo_link_formatter/issues/2697659. Better still: migrate this 'link field' data into media entities, to make them available in the Media Library: https://www.drupal.org/project/media_migration/issues/3247422.

virustotal.note: This module is not composer installable — see https://www.drupal.org/project/virustotal/issues/3241229.

webform_clear.note: This module allows not storing webform submissions in Drupal 7. The Drupal 8 and above Webform module contains a superset of its functionality. See https://www.drupal.org/project/webform_clear/issues/3252072.

webform_invitation.note: This module must be installed manually as it has version requirement conflict with drupal/webform module.

webform_password.note: The Webform Password Field module never had any release in Drupal 7, and never even left the experimental sandbox phase. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

webform_remote_post.note: The Webform Remote Post module is obsolete in Drupal 9; use Webform's built-in 'Remote post' handler.

webform_reply_to.note: This module set a custom "Reply-To" e-mail header in Drupal 7. The Drupal 8 and above Webform module contains a superset of its functionality.

webform_term_opts.note: In the Drupal-9 compatible version of Webform, entity references are natively supported.

webform_validation.note: Some of the features from drupal 7 are now merged in the webform module, only equal values validator's migration is supported through webform_migrate module.

wfm.note: The Webform Multiple module was never stable in Drupal 7, and has been unsupported for a long time. It is recommended to use a different module both on Drupal 7 and 9.

whiteboard.note: This module needs an asset library that must be installed manually — see https://git.drupalcode.org/project/whiteboard/blob/8.x-1.x/README.txt.

workbench_moderation.note: The Workbench Moderation module was replaced by Workflows and Content Moderation in Drupal core. The migration of the corresponding moderation flows and the actual revision moderation state is handled by Workbench Moderation Migrate

wysiwyg.note: This module provides WYSIWYG editing for rich text fields using various WYSIWYG editors for a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality, in the Text Editors module.

wysiwyg_filter.note: This module allows configuring a text format and text editor to apply the same restrictions on a Drupal 7 site. Drupal core now contains a superset of its functionality, in the Text Editors module.

wysiwyg_mediaembed.note: Drupal core now has a media library with text editor integration out-of-the-box. But the migration from the Wysiwyg Media Embed module does not exist yet. Help out at https://www.drupal.org/project/media_migration/issues/3188704.

wysiwyg_template.note: This module must be installed manually — see https://www.drupal.org/project/wysiwyg_template for instructions.

xautoload.note: The X Autoload for Drupal 7 was simply a backport of functionality in Drupal 8.

xmlsitemap_modal.note: The XML sitemap modal UI module was always hidden in Drupal 7, and is part of the main XML Sitemap module in Drupal 9.

xssprotection.note: This module does not have 8|9 port. Nearest module having similar feature is https://www.drupal.org/project/xss_prevention
